<item>
            <title>[SPARK-38273] decodeUnsafeRows&apos;s iterators should close underlying input streams</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-38273</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-34647&quot; title=&quot;Upgrade ZSTD-JNI to 1.4.8-7 and use NoFinalizer classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-34647&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-34647&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; replaced the ZstdInputStream with ZstdInputStreamNoFinalizer. This meant that all usages of `CompressionCodec.compressedInputStream` would need to manually close the stream as this would no longer be handled by GC finaliser mechanism.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In SparkPlan, the result of `CompressionCodec.compressedInputStream` is wrapped in an Iterator which never calls close. This implementation needs to make use of NextIterator which allows for the closing of underlying streams.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
